programme.desc: The Paris Masters. Coverage of the fourth day at the AccorHotels Arena in Paris, featuring matches in the third round. Britain's Andy Murray is the current champion, having defeated American John Isner in last year's final to pick up his first win at this event. The Scot had also reached the previous year's final, but was beaten by Novak Djokovic, who picked up his fourth Paris trophy and third in succession

programme.desc: Wolverhampton Wanderers v Fulham (Kick-off 7.45pm). Coverage of the Championship fixture, which takes place at Molineux. The home side have not lost a league match against the Cottagers since March 2012, when a Pavel Pogrebnyak hat-trick and two goals from Clint Dempsey sealed a 5-0 Premier League win at Craven Cottage. Last year's corresponding fixture finished in a remarkable 4-4 draw in December 2016
